@markusthoemmes makes sense.

I think your idea has the advantage of not also catching catastrophically sick invokers, but additionally catching invokers with occasional problems where only some of the invocations fail. More importantly, it measures the actual invocations of app code - which is what matters.

The proposed 10 minutes seem very high. In my idea I had ~100ms in mind to catch failing invokers (basically the time it realistically takes for a test message to make it through an empty Kafka topic and start the healthcheck action). Maybe your proposal can be enhanced to catch catastrophic invoker failure faster? (as opposed to occasional failure which might take some time to be caught)

